.SH NAME
WebGLVertexArrayObject \- WebGLVertexArrayObject
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]WebGLVertexArrayObject\f[B]\f[R] interface is part of the
WebGL 2 API, represents vertex array objects (VAOs) pointing to vertex
array data, and provides names for different sets of vertex data.
.PP
When working with \f[CR]WebGLVertexArrayObject\f[R] objects, the
following methods are useful:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]WebGL2RenderingContext.createVertexArray()\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]WebGL2RenderingContext.deleteVertexArray()\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]WebGL2RenderingContext.isVertexArray()\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]WebGL2RenderingContext.bindVertexArray()\f[R]
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] The \f[CR]OES_vertex_array_object\f[R] extension allows
you to use vertex array objects in a WebGL 1 context.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] vao = gl.createVertexArray();
gl.bindVertexArray(vao);

\f[I]// \&...\f[R]

\f[I]// calls to bindBuffer or vertexAttribPointer\f[R]
\f[I]// which will be \[dq]recorded\[dq] in the VAO\f[R]

\f[I]// \&...\f[R]
.EE
